The euro fell for a second day
against the dollar after European Central Bank Governing Council
member Nout Wellink was quoted by the Dagblad newspaper as
saying a planned European aid fund may need to be doubled.  The single currency slid 0.4 percent to $1.4122 as of 1:54
p.m. in  Tokyo  from yesterday in  New York .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
